    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-06-04T11:45:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-06-04T11:45:00-05:00" n="784"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d784">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/23456, 23457.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Special Commissioners</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Niagara Falls</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-04T11:45:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 4, 1914, 11.45 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Mediators discuss the wishes of the Governments in such a matter of course
                    way as to show that they do not consider it improper to confer with A. B. C.
                    Governments which according to the official correspondence had tendered their
                    good offices. At our last meeting the Chilean Minister presented a telegram from
                    his Government agreeing with him that an armistice must be required. In view of
                    the consequences that may follow the failure or success of the mediation, we
                    feel justified in calling your attention to this matter before we have another
                    meeting, and to inquire whether you consider that the Mediators are acting as
                    individuals or as the representatives of their Governments and bound to follow
                    their instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Commissioners</hi>.</closer>
                <frus:attachment>
                    <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head"
                        >[Untitled]</head>
                    <opener>
                        <dateline rendition="#right">
                            <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-04T18:25:00">
                                <hi rend="italic">June 4, 1914, 6.25 p.m.</hi>
                            </date>
                        </dateline>
                    </opener>
                    <p>Since our telegram of this morning we have been reading Oppenheim and Moore
                        as to the office of mediation and though they indicate that it is a
                        governmental act they furnish no suggestion as to how far the Mediators can
                        be directed by their Governments. Mr. Lehmann is of the opinion that, the
                        mediation being a governmental function, the Mediators may properly maintain
                        themselves in harmony with the views of their Governments and may properly
                        consult their Governments. Judge Lamar takes a different view, unless their
                        countries are parties.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Commissioners</hi>.</closer>
                </frus:attachment>
            </div>
